<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 2:00AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Pittsburg County
through 245 AM CDT...
At 200 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 4 miles north of Atwood to 2 miles south of Gerty
to 3 miles north of Olney. Movement was east at 50 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Mcalester...                      Hartshorne...
Krebs...                          Kiowa...
Savanna...                        Crowder...
Alderson...                       Ashland...
Haywood...                        Blocker...
Mcalester Regional Airport...     Scipio...
Blanco...                         Haileyville...
Pittsburg...                      Arpelar...
Dow...                            Bache...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
